text: Blountville is a census-designated place (CDP) in and the county seat of Sullivan County, Tennessee, United States. The population was 3,120 at the 2020 census. It is the only Tennessee county seat not to be an incorporated city or town. ==References== Category:County seats in Tennessee Category:Census-designated places in Tennessee Category:Tri-Cities, Tennessee Category:Sullivan County, Tennessee
title: Blountville, Tennessee
